 🎯 Summary :-
Amazon VPC is the foundation of networking in AWS. It provides a secure and isolated virtual network where organizations can deploy applications with complete control over IP addressing, routing, and security.
By combining VPCs, Public and Private Subnets, Internet Gateways, NAT Gateways, Route Tables, and Security Groups, AWS enables you to build scalable, secure, and highly available cloud architectures while protecting critical workloads from unnecessary internet exposure.
